BasicAuthenticationFilter
--------------------------
BasicAuthenticationFilter is created when http basic authentication
[http.httpBasic(Customizer.withDefaults())] enabled in spring security configuration.

It will trigger Condition :Authorization: Basic ... header
Ex: GET /api/data
    Authorization: Basic aGVtYToxMjM=

Interrpt Http request
Reads "Authorization" header.
Extract Base 64 encoded credentails. [Post man send username and password in Base64]
Creates UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken
Passes it to Authentication Manager



UsernamePasswordAuthenticationFilter
-------------------------------------
This filter will be created when we added .form() based login.


Note : If we add both [ http.basic() & form.login() ]based on the request it will be called




BasicAuthenticationFilter Work flow
-----------------------------------
Filter intercepts request
Authorization: Basic ...
   |
Decode credentials
Extracts Base64 string
Decodes:
hema:Sekhar@01
   |
Create
UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken auth =
    new UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken(username, password);
At this point Authneticated = false
   |
Calls AuthenticationManager
authenticationManager.authenticate(auth);
   |
AuthenticationManager delegates
Usually to:
DaoAuthenticationProvider
Which does:
 Load user via UserDetailsService
 Compare password using PasswordEncoder
   |
If authentication SUCCESS
UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken (authenticated = true)
   |
SecurityContextHolder.getContext().setAuthentication(auth);
   |
If authentication FAILS
Throws exception: BadCredentialsException
401 Unauthorized



UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken
------------------------------------
It is a class
It is implementation of the Authentication interface in spring security.

It is used in two phases:

Before Authentication : isAuthenticated = false
Authentication auth = new UsernamePasswordAuthenticationToken("Hema", "Sekhar@01");
       |
AuthenticationManager.authenticate(auth);
       |
After authentication  : isAuthenticated = true



